@@yThe Southern Pyramid@@N

@@eThe Southern Pyramid is the Moon Sovereign's counter-monument: an inverted
theology in architecture. What appears from the surface to be a modest
funerary complex is only the anchor point of an immense downward-engineered
state crypt, descending through seven tiers consecrated to aspects of death.@@N

@@dThe Moon Sovereign, twin sibling and bitter rival of the Sand Sovereign,
rejected the Solar Court's doctrine that sunlight was law made visible.
Instead, the Moon Sovereign declared that true authority lay below, in the
underworld's root-systems of death that the Solar Court had tried to
domesticate. Each descending tier binds a death-function as administrative
domain:@@N

@@y  Silence  @@d- suppression of dissent and witness control
@@y  Decay    @@d- managed ruin and reclamation from the dead
@@y  Shadow   @@d- surveillance through concealment
@@y  Bone     @@d- genealogy and legitimacy through remains
@@y  Venom    @@d- punishment refined to chemical efficiency
@@y  Fire     @@d- irreversible judgment and purification
@@y  Void     @@d- sovereign exception beyond all rite and law@@N

@@eThese seven aspects systematically invert the Solar Court's seven virtues
of kingship. Each tier was designed to demonstrate that the Solar Court's
virtues were merely domesticated versions of death forces that the underworld
controlled more completely.@@N

@@rThe volcanic glass lake at the nadir was designed as a controlled interface
with the anti-light source. The Moon Sovereign believed the Black Sun Shard
was not alien but a natural emanation of the underworld. Rather than contain
it, the Sovereign sought to learn its grammar.@@N

@@dThe Eclipsed Tongues, the Moon Sovereign's theological faction, survived the
pyramid's sealing and merged with the Jackal Synod of the Eastern Desert,
injecting underworld-descent theology into what had been a purely solar cult.
Modern Synod members who speak of 'the eclipse that cleanses' unknowingly
channel Moon Sovereign doctrine filtered through centuries of corruption.@@N
